<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
A scavenger, taken in baited traps (
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, K" journalOrPublisher="Fisheries Science" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="721 - 730" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1444-2906.2005.01021.x" refId="B98" refString="Ide, K, Sasaki, K, Omori, M, 2005. Food intake and digestion in the scavenging lysianassid gammaridean Scopelocheirus onagawae. Fisheries Science 71 (4): 721 - 730, DOI: 10.1111/j.1444-2906.2005.01021.x" title="Food intake and digestion in the scavenging lysianassid gammaridean Scopelocheirus onagawae." url="10.1111/j.1444-2906.2005.01021.x" volume="71" year="2005">Ide et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
), and also known to attack injured flounder juveniles under laboratory conditions (
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, K" journalOrPublisher="Fisheries Science" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1209 - 1214" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1444-2906.2006.01278.x" refId="B100" refString="Ide, K, Takahashi, K, Sasaki, K, Omori, M, 2006b. Predation by scavenging amphipods to injured hatchery-raised juvenile Japanese flounder Paralichthys olivaceus under laboratory conditions. Fisheries Science 72 (6): 1209 - 1214, DOI: 10.1111/j.1444-2906.2006.01278.x" title="Predation by scavenging amphipods to injured hatchery-raised juvenile Japanese flounder Paralichthys olivaceus under laboratory conditions." url="10.1111/j.1444-2906.2006.01278.x" volume="72" year="2006 b">Ide et al. 2006b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation author="Takekawa, AT" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="681 - 687" publicationUrl="10.2108/zsj.17.681" refId="B192" refString="Takekawa, AT, Ishimaru, S, 2000. A new species of the genus Scopelocheirus (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea) from Onagawa Bay, northeastern Japan. Zoological Science 17: 681 - 687, DOI: 10.2108/zsj.17.681" title="A new species of the genus Scopelocheirus (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea) from Onagawa Bay, northeastern Japan." url="10.2108/zsj.17.681" volume="17" year="2000">Takekawa and Ishimaru (2000)</bibRefCitation>
originally placed this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1857" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Scopelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the lack of a setal fringe on the coxae of the anterior pereopods. In the present study we have revised the diagnoses for these genera and excluded this character from the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1911" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Aroui" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aroui" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Aroui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We are therefore removing this species from the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1857" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Scopelocheirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1911" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Aroui" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aroui" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Aroui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on maxilla 2, of which the outer plate is shorter than the inner plate and bears long, distally barbed slender setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
